# Review of "review external audit" — BS detection pass

**Method**: Dispatched 6 parallel verification agents against the file:line anchors in the audit. Each claim checked against current code. Verdict column: **REAL** (claim matches code), **BS** (claim contradicts code), **STALE** (claim was true but has shipped), **PARTIAL** (partially true, mis-stated), **UNVERIFIED** (not spot-checked this pass).

**Date**: 2026-04-24. Branch tip the audit cites: `ed4944e`. Current tip: `e27a00c`.

---

## TL;DR

Most of the audit stands up. Of ~120 load-bearing claims I spot-checked, **~85% REAL**, **~5% BS**, **~10% PARTIAL/STALE**. The generator is technically competent; where it errs, it errs by overclaiming severity ("Critical" on posture decisions) and by fabricating a handful of specific claims without reading far enough. The file:line anchors are mostly accurate.

**The "critical" tier is mixed**: some are genuinely ship-blocking (GG.1 follows `OR true`, BBB.2 kids entitlements, T.3 persist_generated_article rollback risk), others are posture opinions framed as critical (PP.1–PP.4 performance, RR.3 iOS observability, UU.1 TS strict).

**Biggest BS flags** (stop here if you only read one section):
- **K.2** claims six admin pages have NO client-side permission gate. **All six do.** Verified directly.
- **RR.1** claims ~3 of 216 API routes emit to Sentry. **Agent found 100 with Sentry/safeErrorResponse integration.** Audit dramatically undercounted.
- **BBB.1** (labeled CRITICAL) claims VerityPostKids has no Info.plist. **The file exists** at `VerityPostKids/VerityPostKids/Info.plist`. Partial — the *contents* may still be missing Kids-Category keys, but the "file doesn't exist" framing is wrong.
- **BB.2** — `log_ad_impression` RPC is not in schema/110 at all. Audit invented the function or it was never written. Either way, the budget-cap-enforcement claim needs re-framing.
- **FF.2** — cites `comment_reports` table; actual table is `reports`. Drift in the audit itself.

